metadata.name: Pipes  #54
metadata.description:
In his 2023 book, 'The Beauty of Play', Frank Lantz writes, 'Games are an aesthetic form. Which is to say they are something we do for their own sake, in search of beauty, pleasure and meaning, a realm in which our subjective tastes and individual experiences are joined together into communities of critical judgement and overlapping but contested values'.



'Pipes' is a reimagining of the game 'Pipe Mania', released in 1990 by Empire Software. While in the original game, the aim for the player is to connect a series of randomly generated pipe pieces to ensure the flow of 'goo' for a specified distance, in 'Pipes', unique left-to right-pathways are generated section by section.



By refiguring this game and its components into a generative collection, 'Pipes' forms a part of an overarching series, 'The Art of Play', which seeks to highlight the aesthetic beauty of early gaming software.

metadata.name: A Stitch Is Fine #42
metadata.description:
Favorites are held together with stitching. Deep weaves of fabric. A patch of solid color. Intricate patterns created by layers of thread.

There are no rarity attributes assigned to this artwork, its value is intended to be determined by viewer aesthetic alone.

This artwork was created using p5js.

linktr.ee/lisaorthstudio
twitter: @lisaorthstudio

metadata.name: WTBS: Wearable #1 (cap edition) #1
metadata.description:
The Waiting is over. It’s actually happening. We’ve teased, hinted, and honestly YEARNED for this release. We hope you enjoy.

WTBS: Wearable #1 (cap edition) is a celebration of the 3rd anniversary of the Waiting To Be Signed Podcast. We mark this milestone in collaboration with artist Anna Lucia and are extremely pleased to bring you these one-of-a-kind generative caps. Each NFT in this series is an animated digital artwork which contains the embroidery design for a unique cap. When you obtain an NFT from this collection, you’re not only collecting digital art, you can also redeem a cap featuring the very design! 

Get your cap: 

Anna Lucia has curated a full collection using fx(hash)’s params function. At the time of sale, all NFTs will have already been minted by Anna Lucia & ready for sale. You can acquire your preferred design by placing an offer of $75 or more (in TEZ equivalent), which will be accepted by Anna. This price includes the NFT & cap but excludes shipping. Cap redemption will be handled via Artfora.com. 
If you are not buying the cap directly from Anna Lucia’s wallet (tz1M7dt8sWC64ZXkmiWbttVCtgFrFU6Do9x9), please view the collection on Artfora to check whether the cap has already been redeemed or not. 

Controls:

The NFT itself showcases the dynamic, animated generative design. Use the interactive controls to explore variations and preview how your chosen design will look on the embroidered cap. There are two colors cap, black and desert beige, represented by the background color and reflected in the mock-up. 

A -> Toggle between animated view and cap mock-up
D -> Download the embroidery file 
E -> Detailed view of embroidery design 
R -> Record and download a .zip file of 300 frames

On mobile only the digital animated view is available. 

This work is created with p5.js and stitch.js.

metadata.name: Resilience  #85
metadata.description:
Resilience is a collection of endless architectures.
In a resilient generative system composed of multiple compatible parts, real-time information exchange enables open reconfigurations and continuous discrete adjustments. Sometimes vague and fuzzy, sometimes real and tangible, they reveal different readings of architectural complexity and scale: from city plans to floor plans and details to sections and elevations.

Resilience comes in a variety of polychrome palettes, ascii glyphs, and styles. 
To enjoy it in full-screen mode, press the left mouse button in live mode, for a monochrome look press 'b'. Made with P5js.

Resilience Generative Token by @grasser_alex 2022

metadata.name: Microgravity #412
metadata.description:
Microgravity is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022.

Scale symmetry of abstract semiliquid forms.

Click on a section of the image to explore deeper.

- Use the "R" key to reset the coordinates.

metadata.name: Ataraxis #16
metadata.description:
Ataraxis (or a broken volume renderer) is an exploration in balancing discomfort and calm. The piece generates spaces on the fly that are designed to elicit strange and uncomfortable feelings - like a desolate, alien dreamscape - claustrophobic, surreal, not quite real yet strangely recognisable. But the idea is that while these spaces feel uncomfortable, they're also strangely, antilogically calming. The idea is to elicit a sanguine emotion, to make the viewer feel calm in a strange place, and to lead them somewhere else.

This work is the culmination of many years of work researching volumetric rendering techniques. This token uses a raymarching technique that is intentionally broken in various ways.

Controls:
Double-click to download
&w=X&h=y to change the size of the piece
&dpr=x to change the resolution of the pice - higher resolutions will result in slightly different artworks as the browser attempts to compensate for the overlarge canvas
&fullscreen=true to change the token to display the full size of your browser. This may impact the rendering of the token, so use with caution

metadata.name: Ersbla #23
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

Sketches of geometric shapes with scale symmetry.

"What does the mirror see when it looks in the mirror?"

--

metadata.name: Penumbra #102
metadata.description:
Penumbra is a geometric exploration of the possible outcomes from 3 basic rules:

1) Place some walls
2) Place some light sources
3) Draw the resulting shadows

This series is a small thank you to the collectors of Umbra :)

metadata.name: 8x8 Pixel Creatures #96
metadata.description:
Pixel art is a highly relevant art form, which rarely gets the kudos it deserves from the wider art world. 

I wanted to include some small pixel art creations in another project I was working on. However, I got a bit carried away, and ended up creating a pixel creature generator.

I came to like these little pixel creatures, so I decided to share them, and give them a life on FxHash - I hope you like them too. 

There are a bunch of variations, and a reasonable chance one or two styles may never be minted, so mint away, and I hope you get a rare one. Also, minters get a share in future royalties of their mints, which may be cool in any reality where they become popular one day.

I'll probably reference these guys on other relevant art I produce, when it seems appropriate.

Coded in p5js.

metadata.name: System β #30
metadata.description:
α -> β is about "Increases in magnitude and decreases in computation". And still related the fleeting time in the generating process.

My role in this work is more of a discoverer than a creator. 

Try to reveal the possibilities of time perception in the generative art through negotiating with incomprehensible mathematical equations.

What I want to explore through this work is that behind the generated results, the dynamic process of generations are equally diverse and unpredictable.

When we watch the generating process displayed on the computer, changing instantly, moving, multiplying, disappearing, and we hesitate, wonder, pause, await, as if many possibilities of time perception have emerged in the fragmented moments.

_
press [1] -> β 
press [2] -> β⁰　 
press [3] -> β¹
-
Press [s] in live view to save as PNG.
Press [d] in live view to save as hi-res PNG.
-
If you need your collection in SVG format, feel free to DM me.

metadata.name: Reflejos #34
metadata.description:
Reflejos es un proyecto de arte generativo diseñado para existir en la blockchain de Tezos. Este proyecto se aloja en la plataforma fx(hash) y genera obras de arte únicas utilizando un algoritmo y un sistema numérico hexadecimal que se crea con cada nuevo token.

Este proyecto fue desarrollado utilizando la librería p5.js de JavaScript, creada por Lauren Lee McCarthy. Reflejos es el resultado de la interacción entre la percepción humana y un conjunto de reglas interpretadas por la máquina.

Inspirado por la experiencia de caminar junto al mar y los estados de calma y contemplación que esta actividad puede evocar, Reflejos busca entrelazar a los espectadores con las obras de la colección. 

La intención es motivar al espectador a explorar su interior y descubrir momentos de apertura perceptiva. 

El objetivo es que la obra provoque una sensación de calma y claridad en el espectador a través de una conexión íntima y personal.
